  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bb5\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b86\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nation Will Paralyze - Central Bank Governor Warns",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Central Bank Governor Nandalal Weerasinghe has warned that if a stable government is not established, the country may be completely paralyzed. He told this to BBC's Newsnight.",
        "He also mentioned that there is great uncertainty about the availability of foreign exchange for essential petroleum imports.",
        "He noted that receiving international bailout funds depended on a stable government.",
        "The country is in the grip of great unrest due to the massive economic crisis. President Gotabaya Rajapaksa has fled the country and in response, President Ranil Wickremesinghe has issued a curfew for the second day.",
        "Sri Lanka is facing its economic downturn as the prices of basic commodities for the common man including food and fuel have increased drastically.",
        "Many blame the Rajapakses' mishandling of the economy, with Ranil Wickremesinghe, who became prime minister in May, part of the problem.",
        "Nandalal Weerasinghe, who took over as the Central Bank Governor in April, said that he did not know how essential goods could be provided without a stable administration.",
        "\"By the end of this month we will be able to pay for three diesel ships and one or two petrol ships, but beyond that there is a lot of uncertainty about whether we can provide the foreign exchange to get enough petrol for the country,\" he told the BBC.",
        "He said that if the foreign exchange cannot be provided, the entire country is in danger of being paralyzed. Because of this, there is a need for a presidential cabinet that can take decisions. If there is no such thing, the people will be in crisis.",
        "The central bank governor has said that we would like to see better progress by holding talks with the lenders on debt restructuring but how fast this can be done depends on the stable governance and once a stable government is in place Sri Lanka can recover from the crisis in three to four months."
      ],
